<!-- scope: human-approved 2026-05-22 M1.10 self-refresh — weekly freshness check + auto-file refresh tasks; operator directive "add a mechanism so that minsky keeps competitors list updated and competitors there too"; closes the corpus-staleness loop with rule-#17 healing (observed staleness IS the fix). -->
<!--
Minsky weekly corpus-freshness check + auto-file — launchd LaunchAgent
for macOS.

Pattern: "periodic task" supervisor pattern (Borg/Bashir/Burns/Hightower
_Designing Distributed Systems_ 2017). Every Monday at 04:15 local
(15 min after the weekly-competitive scoreboard refresh) launchd fires
`run-corpus-refresh-check.sh` which:
  1. Runs `node scripts/check-corpus-freshness.mjs` to score the corpus.
  2. If any entry is "very-stale" (>180 days), invokes
     `node scripts/auto-file-corpus-refresh-tasks.mjs` to append
     `corpus-refresh-<id>` task blocks to TASKS.md.
  3. Commits the TASKS.md edit (if any), so the tick-loop picks it up
     and invokes /competitor-research <url> to refresh the reading.

Why this exists
---------------
M1.10 acceptance: "scorecard updates weekly". The scorecard itself is
already weekly-refreshed by com.minsky.weekly-competitive.plist. THIS
plist closes the corpus-staleness loop: it ensures the SOURCE numbers
the scorecard joins against also stay fresh, by surfacing very-stale
readings as filed tasks.

Schedule: Monday 04:15 (15 min after the weekly-competitive scoreboard
refresh at 04:00, so the freshness JSON is read against the just-
refreshed corpus state).

Placeholders substituted by `bin/minsky install-daemon` via envsubst:
  ${MINSKY_HOME}   — absolute path to the minsky repo checkout
  ${HOME}          — operator's home directory
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.minsky.corpus-refresh-check</string>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>MINSKY_HOME</key>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>
        <key>PATH</key>
        <string>/usr/local/bin:/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/bin:/bin</string>
    </dict>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/bin/bash</string>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/distribution/systemd/run-corpus-refresh-check.sh</string>
    </array>

    <!--
    StartCalendarInterval: Monday at 04:15 local time. 15 min after
    com.minsky.weekly-competitive.plist (which refreshes the scorecard
    at 04:00) so the freshness check reads against the post-scoreboard-
    rebuild state.
    -->
    <key>StartCalendarInterval</key>
    <dict>
        <key>Weekday</key>
        <integer>1</integer>
        <key>Hour</key>
        <integer>4</integer>
        <key>Minute</key>
        <integer>15</integer>
    </dict>

    <!--
    RunAtLoad: surface staleness on host bootstrap so a fresh install
    immediately sees what needs refreshing without waiting until Monday.
    -->
    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
    Cycle cap: 120s. The freshness check + the auto-file walk are both
    pure local-file operations, so anything longer is a bug.
    -->
    <key>HardResourceLimits</key>
    <dict>
        <key>CPU</key>
        <integer>120</integer>
    </dict>

    <!--
    Logs go to ~/.local/state/minsky/corpus-refresh.log per the
    AGENTS.md convention for scheduled-task logs.
    -->
    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>${HOME}/.local/state/minsky/corpus-refresh.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>${HOME}/.local/state/minsky/corpus-refresh.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
